        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 8:12PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 812 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southeast of Fourche Valley, or 17 miles south of Danville,
moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Plainview in Yell County...       Avant...
Carter Cove Park...               Rover...
Kingston...                       Mt Tabor...
Fannie...                         Fourche Mountain Recreation Are...
Onyx...                           Sunlight Bay Park...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
